thin my first three swings with a War Cleaver (best 2h axe), I won't use a 2h.  The defensive cost of not having a shield is too great when the slightly increased damage is only temporary. <p><i>"People will believe any lie you give them; whether it is because they wish it to be true, or fear it to be true." -<b>Wizard's First Rule</i></b><Br><Br><b>Mundus Vult Decipi</b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uubergnome563.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ubergnome563</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/4/02 1:35:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2016.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> Even a miss or 2 wouldnt have made a difference<br><br>1 hit with the 2h was worth about 2-3 full dual wield double swings.  Its just mad unbalancing as is.  Granted LA sucks from what i hear, but in no way do the other rogue classes stack up meleewise, which is all we have for a base (same envenom possibility, CS, etc) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unyvinyd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nyvinyd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/4/02 2:38:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2016.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.jurassic5.com/images/index_logo.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> Left axe is great with ninja weapons (dual hand axes rock).  However, you have to spam styles. <p><center><img src=http://www.rockapella.com/IMAGES/rocktype.gif></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usmudgedaemelar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Smudge DaeMelar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://cwmonkey.virtualave.net/s/net8/laghost.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/4/02 7:11:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2016.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> 2Hers hurt like hell if they hit but if you get lucky with evades/misses... it can really hurt the person using the slow weapon. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uphaelondaoc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Phaelon DAoC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/4/02 7:25:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2016.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> ...but if you get lucky with evades/misses... <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>Does this happen in RvR?  I've seen many posts saying evade is next to useless in RvR.  I havent done enough to know for sure though. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usmudgedaemelar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Smudge DaeMelar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://cwmonkey.virtualave.net/s/net8/laghost.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/4/02 7:37:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2016.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Does this happen in RvR? I've seen many posts saying evade is next to useless in RvR. I havent done enough to know for sure though. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>Well... thats why I said lucky. It is probally considered useless because we die in 1-3 hits. I did have a lucky streak with an orange con hunter that was taking 250 point hits on me...but I evaded 6 times in the whole fight and killed him. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=majin>Majin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/4/02 8:52:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2016.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> Well, did you expected something else from a midgard class ?<br><br>hehe <br><br><br>\/ <p><img border=0 src=http://members.tripod.de/majin_mlf/midgard_ownz_small.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usammyd11.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sammyd11</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/4/02 9:45:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2016.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> I am a Nightshade and I have owned yellow and orange con infiltrators if I got off my PA first (especially now that it destealths you).  So it comes down to whoever gets off the first hit, that's balanced enough for me.  I soloed a yellow con minstral last night as well, which made me very very happy.  Didn't even get off my PA on him, just my poisons and some nice melee.<br><br>I took out a shadowblade two night ago (yellow con) and he was hitting for 120-130, I was hitting for 40-50, I was at 3/4 health when it was over and I didn't use PA, just poisons.  Ever since they made it easier to see stealthed peeps, I hardly ever get PA off so I am depending on the poisons more.  Even blue cons see me very easily with 41 stealth at lv42. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usammyd11.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sammyd11</A> at: 2/4/02 1:51:30 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uubergnome563.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ubergnome563</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/4/02 1:14:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2016.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> I one shotted a 48ish nightshade with perf.  There should some kinda law in hibernia forbiding lurikeens from entering melee combat.<br><br>But this isnt about perf, poison, or anything else other than pure melee.  a blue con, who is at least 5 levels lower, shadowblade can own a higher level infil / probally nightshade in raw melee output using a 2h.<br><br>Point being:<br><br>They get the same evenom / CS / stealth, and MORE general melee.  The slowness of the sword does not matter either, in that the best perf thrust weapon out there so far in albion in a 3.5 gladius, which is slow in and of itself, and lacks the additional bonus that 2 handers get to compensate for the difference in raw damage.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukrugkopf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krugkopf</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/5/02 12:35:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2016.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> ubergnome, pardon me for saying this, but you seem to be jumping to very hasty conclusions.  You got killed by a blue.  It happens in the Frontier.  RvR encounters are nothing like PvE encounters.  I've been killed outright by blues on several occasions, nearly killed by a single green, etc, not to mention the orange/red/purple deaths.  At the same time I've managed to bag 1 red, 3 oranges, 1 yellow, and 5 blues.<br><br>I'll repeat, I've been jumped by a blue several times, and died.  Most of those times, I had out my 2h and missed.<br><br>At the same time, I've been jumped by a yellow several times, and died.  Most of the few times I survived with a lot of health left over was because of a few lucky 2h hits, but at the same time I stood a better chance of living using my 1h w/ shield.<br><br>For every miss with a 2h weapon, that is 2-3 misses of a 1h weapon, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> plus</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> the damage from the styles accompanying.  Using a 2h weapon does nothing more than increase your potential damage, at the same time decreasing your minimum potential damage.  It's a gamblers weapon.  When stealth attacking, the odds are usually in the wielder's favor.  Otherwise, it's a toss-up.<br><br>If I feel that the enemy is going to be hitting me, I will <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> always</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> switch to a fast 1h w/ shield.  To do so otherwise is to gamble my life on even odds.  With the 1h w/ shield, I can take advantage of styles other than Stealth chains, including the Hamstring line (which I pull off nearly every battle with a 1h, doing more damage in the long run than my 2h).  Also, because I can pull off these defensive styles, my defense shoots through the roof (Hamstring increases your defense, which I think helps me to evade even more...).<br><br>I seriously don't want to get into an argument about this.  If I wanted &quot;this class can do this better, thus we should get this...&quot; discussions, I'd visit the Vault boards.  I <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> could</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> start mentioning the fact that assassins of other realms can actually use multiple poisons because they have assassin friendly dual wields, but where would that get me?<br><br>To sum up:  2 handed weapons help with the stealthed attacks, as the target takes a moment to respond.<br><br>In melee <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> on average</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, fast hitting 1h or multiple 1h weapons are better, because the lessened effect misses have.<br><br>All weapon skill being equal, of course. <p><i>"People will believe any lie you give them; whether it is because they wish it to be true, or fear it to be true." -<b>Wizard's First Rule</i></b><Br><Br><b>Mundus Vult Decipi</b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uubergnome563.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ubergnome563</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/5/02 1:15:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2016.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> If it was just one encounter, i would write it off as nothing.<br><br>This is a consistant thing that has happened on multiple occasions, that somebody 5 -6 levels lower of the same class architype shouldnt be able to do for sheer inequality reasons alone.  <br><br>in melee on average, 2 handed weapons are much superiour to 1 handed fast weapons, because of the sheer bonuses they recieve to damage, especially since dual wield / celtic on an assassin on average is nowwhere near the spec required to make it effective and reliable.<br><br>Regardless of  opinion, fast weapons dont get 3 hits in per 1 hit of a 2 hander, yet they only do about 1/4 to 1/5th the damage.  And when you compare hp, it doesnt really matter considering you only need 4 hits with a 2h, to my 12-18 with a 1h fast weapon. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucaithcaidh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caith Caidh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/5/02 1:32:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2016.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> Erm... I always felt that left axe was far more envenom friendly than Alb or Hib duals... You're guaranteed to swing both each time... For Albion or Hib, you MAY swing both.  Either can miss when swinging both, but in general I would think that Shadowblades using left axe will (on the average) land a shot with each envenomed weapon before an average inf or shade.  I guess it's just that I don't agree with the comment about Hib and Alb having an advantage in that department...  You have 3 choices:  weapon + shield, weapon + axe, or big weapon.  We have 2:  Weapon and shield, or weapon and other weapon.  If you compare the weapon + weapon setups SBs have the advantage:  They can guarantee that both weapons will be swung in the first round.  Assuming we all have an equal chance to hit, this certainly outstrips the 25% chance that I have to swing both, as a nightshade.  If I get unlucky, I could be waiting all fight for that second weapon to even swing...  <br>Knowing one's own abilities is key, both in PvE and in RvR.  A large part of this is being consistant, and whatever problems Left Axe may have, (I am unfamiliar with it at more than a cursory level) it is at least predictable.<br><br> <p><IMG SRC="http://www.dopplex.net/sigfile2.jpg" ALT="Caith Caidh, 35th Season Nightshade, An Claidheamh Soluis" ALIGN="middle"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=majin>Majin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/5/02 2:16:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2016.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> Caith Caidh, thats not true, every class can use 2h. You can use staves, i dont know why you always forget that so you have the same abilities as SBs have.<br><br>Furthermore its utterly useless to use a left axe skill if you dont train much (very much) in it. DW is alot more powerful than left axe, if you hit so low with the left axe there is no point that the poison gives an advantage if you could do 3x times more damage with your 2h. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uubergnome563.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ubergnome563</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/5/02 2:48:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2016.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> there are no staffs in existance in albion (and i could guess and say hibernia) that are matching dps to their 1 handed counterparts, and even then its not trainable like a weapon spec.<br><br>think the biggest staff (infilable) in albion is an ebon wood shod staff make by a fletcher. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uciardhasidhe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ciardha Sidhe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/5/02 9:36:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2016.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.starseer.com/nightshade/ciardha60a.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: heh here is class balance for you...</span><hr size=1> We can use staves, yes, but we can't train in them.  Big difference. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucroverdarogue.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CroverDaRogue</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/5/02 11:28:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2016.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~skysprite/_uimages/sig.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: heh here is class balance for you...</span><hr size=1> Here are some SB pvp observations, if they help a wee bit.<br><br>When fighting other realm rogues, I go L axe for the bonuses I recieve from both weapons (Hps, + to axe skill, str). Only time I will use 2h on other stealthers is if they con blue and I think I can one-shot them with my 2h axe.<br><br>Evade does work in pvp, but probably not as well as it does PVE. <br><br>2h does own for one shotting people, but not as much as it used to. In general melee I will still go Left Axe to get as many hits as I can in. I enjoy the fact that  as long as I hit someone (I do not have to keel em) and someone/something else kills em, I still get Rps <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . The new buffs, and the general increased awareness of other players against getting one shot killed has really slowed this method down. As far as folks thinking 2h weaps are slow enough to make sloths snort in derision...well, we have ass loads of quick...Im at 149 quick at lvl 44 atm, and thats with a concious effort to NOT get quick gear, but +str/Hps/slash/blunt resist gear. So misses arent as bad as one might think.<br><br>Left axe takes alot of points (at least 30) to become on par with our 2h dmg lvls, and that makes Sbs have to spread our points even further, comparatively. However, the swing-each-time-guaranteed is pretty darn spiffy.<br><br>Overall, I really do feel Sbs pack the most punch for the dollar against our other realm bretheren. We still have some balancing issues that need attending (I just love being full mana 100% of the time), so I can only see the relative strength growing.<br><br>Sinatra Fabulous<br>44 Sb, lover<br>Palo <p><img src="http://morganfl.tripod.com//sitebuildercontent/sitebuilderpictures/sig.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showMessageRange?topicID=2016.topic&start=21&stop=35>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showPrevMessage?topicID=2016.topic"> << Prev Top